This is a full-time position with the Department of Transportation. For more information on the Department of Transportation, please visit https://dot.sd.gov/.
The SD DOT Division of Planning & Engineering is seeking a motivated individual of junior, senior, or graduate level status working towards a B.S. in Civil Engineering that is interested in an opportunity for an educational scholarship and intern position that would transition into permanent employment with the SD DOT following graduation. Permanent employment with SD DOT provides a rewarding career with opportunities for advancement, a flexible work schedule, and great benefits.
This position identifies and develops projects through analysis of potential needs related to highway safety, all aspects of road and bridge condition, and highway capacity. Position responsibilities are tightly related to SDDOT Mission to efficiently provide a safe and effective public transportation system. Project management responsibilities include the definition of project purpose and need, design parameters, resource requirements, project schedule, cost estimates, and communication needs necessary to address a wide variety of highway transportation related maintenance and construction needs. Successful applicant will analyze, prioritize, and combine needs into feasible projects; be responsible for cost estimates used in development of multiple project alternatives and conducting benefit/cost analyses on options; and recommend priorities for project development in appropriate fiscal years based on efficiency, effectiveness, and economical advantage.
A typical 40-hour work week, Monday through Friday, can be expected; although, hours may vary including overtime and some weekends.
Licenses and Certifications:
Bachelor's degree in civil engineering for entry-level position.
The Ideal Candidate Will Have:
Applicants in their junior, senior, or graduate level status pursuing a Bachelor of Science Degree in Civil is preferred.
